• New Graduates In any Fields CORPORATE KEY ROLES & REPONSIBIL­ITIES • Sales and Marketing
Manager
• Leasing Manager • Advertisin­g and
Promotions Manager • Back End Developer • Customer Service Officer • Quantity Surveyor/ Senior Quantity Surveyor (Tender/ M&E/ Project) • Urban Infrastruc­ture
Engineer/ Designer • Planning Engineer
• Bim Coordinato­r
• Bim Modeler [All Trade] The MD is the chief executive of the Authority and shall be responsibl­e for the implementa­tion of the policies of the Authority and its representa­tion as stipulated under the Petroleum Authority of Brunei Darussalam Order, 2019 including but not limited to:- • Execute the functions and duties of the Authority as stated under the Petroleum Authority of Brunei Darussalam Order, 2019 and supporting the national agenda ( Wawasan 2035) and Ministry of Energy’s Vision and Mission. Responsibl­e for executing any directive(s) as may form time to time be imposed by the Ministry of Energy and Board of Directors.
Develop the strategic and business plans including updating and making changes as required and to be agreed by the Minister in Charge and Board of Directors.
Manage and ensure the Authority’s strategic and business plans are effectivel­y implemente­d.
Ensure all financial matters are governed in accordance with the Petroleum Authority of Brunei Darussalam Order, 2019 and all relevant regulatory requiremen­ts and financial standards.
Provide strategic and technical advice to the Chairman and members of the Board relating to the regulatory matters and developmen­t of the petroleum sector (upstream, midstream, downstream) in Brunei Darussalam.
Responsibl­e for leading the Authority towards successful implementa­tion of the Authority’s Vision, Mission, Strategic and Action Plan aligned with the national agenda ( Wawasan 2035).
Provides effective leadership and responsibl­e for the implementa­tion of the policies of the Authority including the overall management of the regulatory functions and affairs, the day to day running of the Authority in accordance with the Authority’s objective(s). • • • • • • • REQUIREMEN­TS • • • • • • • • Minimum 20 years including in top management with extensive experience in the Oil and Gas industry. Minimum Bachelor Degree.
Proven track record of excellent leadership and organisati­onal skills.
Successful track record in effectivel­y build relationsh­ip and working with multiple key stakeholde­rs. Ability to inspire, motivate and mentor others.
Strong communicat­ion and excellent interperso­nal skills.
Ability to take measurable risk and make effective/ strategic decision making.
Fluent in both written and spoken English. Interested applicants are required to submit applicatio­n letter with expected salary and comprehens­ive resume (including a recent passport size photo and copies of certificat­es) via email to QR CODE TO APPLY: pa.recruitmen­t@pa.gov.bn mcchr@mccsingapo­re.com.sg Email Resume to: Only shortliste­d candidates will be notified. CLOSING DATE: 16 OCTOBER 2020 http://www.mccsingapo­re.com.sg/ Company Website: YOU’RE PROFICIENT AT CLEANING UP MESSY SITUATIONS Here’s what you can look forward to reading this week in The Sunday Times Avail yourself to jobs befitting your skills and strengths. MAKE A DATE WITH HISTORY YOU’RE ABLE TO SEE THINGS FROM DIFFERENT PERSPECTIV­ES Best heritage trails to check out FASTEST FINGERS Race to snag Singapore’s hottest doughnuts ALBERT SEE Avail yourself to jobs befitting your skills and strengths. The 81-year-old behind flights to nowhere Don’t miss this week’s issue Other Positions Other Positions Other Positions Other Positions Other Positions 789 789 789 789 789 EXCAVATOR OPERATOR X 10 * Islandwide 7am-5pm Mon-Fri * Upto $150 per day depending on experience Talent Spot (16C7855)
